title: PandaPandas
extract: From Longman Dictionary of Contemporary English. Related topics: Animals. pan‧da /ˈpændə/ noun [countable] 1 a large black and white animal that looks like a bear and lives in the mountains of China2 a small animal with red-brown fur and a long tail that lives in the southeastern Himalayas.
